data.title: Christina Hall jumps right back to work as she is seen for first time on The Flip Off set in California after divorce news from husband and co-star Josh
data.meta_description: The 41-year-old HGTV star - who is already shutting down men from sending her love letters - got back to work on set of The Flip Off in San Clemente, California on Wednesday.
data.text:
Christina Hall was seen for the first time on set of her reality series after divorce news from husband and co-star Josh Hall.

The 41-year-old HGTV star - who is already shutting down men from sending her love letters - got back to work on set of The Flip Off in San Clemente, California on Wednesday.

As she stars on the series with her 43-year-old estranged husband Josh, it is interesting to note that he was nowhere to be seen.

The blonde beauty seemed in good spirits despite the tumultuous time in her personal life as she was all smiles during the day of filming.

She sported multiple athleticwear looks for the long day of filming as she arrived in her white luxury car.

This comes amid news that she is already fielding love letters following her split from her third husband Josh Hall.

The HGTV star shut down the suitors in a funny message posted to her Instagram Stories on Thursday.

'Dear men,' she wrote. 'Your hand written/typed letters are cute but no you will not be my 4th husband,' she concluded with a silly tongue-out emoji.

It came a month after Hall filed for divorce from Josh, 43, following just two years of marriage.

The couple wed in April 2022 before they both filed for divorce from one another last month, and Josh was pictured moving out of their Newport Beach home over the weekend.

Christina's post also contained shout-outs to realtors and people giving her parenting advice.

'Dear fellow realtors - please stop mailing and dropping expensive packets, I am not listing my home...' she wrote. 'But if I were to list it, I would list it myself as I am a real estate agent,' she said with a chin-scratching emoji.

She finished it off with a seemingly sarcastic message to those who had been offering her family and relationship advice.

'Thank you for all the advice about my children and marriages. I really appreciate it,' Christina posted with an emoji covering their eyes.

Josh recently made his first public statement amid the divorce, taking to Instagram to share a selfie of him resting his head on his dog in a solemn post.

He wrote in the caption: 'I prefer privacy, especially during something as life changing as a divorce I did not ask for.'

Without naming Christina, he vowed, 'I will not publicly badmouth anyone as people have families, friends and others who respect and love them. Unfortunately the internet is forever.'

Engaging his 92.3K followers, Hall continued: 'We are real humans, this is our life and I am not here to entertain people I dont know with my private matters. Those details will be handled fairly behind closed doors with our respective counsels in due time. Those who know each of us, know who we are.'

Christina and Josh both filed for divorce, with the former listing their date of separation as July 7 while the latter wrote July 8.

A source told Us Weekly this past weekend that the soon-to-be exes 'havent even started negotiations' in their divorce proceedings.

The couple tied the knot in 2022 and did not sign a prenup.

Josh is seeking a 50/50 division of assets, meanwhile, in a July social media statement, Christina stated that she does not intend to split her personal assets equally.

In an Instagram story, she declared: 'I have worked my a** off to build this life for myself and my children and anyone who would try and take what they do not deserve / what they did NOT work for should be ashamed.'

The message continued, 'An insecure man with a large ego can sure try to derail you  but still I rise.'

After Josh shared a message about 'hope' on his Instagram Stories late last month, Christina took a screenshot of the picture and added her response.

'I "HOPE" she pays me millions more than what she's already offered me,' she wrote in an aggressive swipe at her ex.

Weeks after the back-to-back divorce filings, Christina accused her estranged husband of transferring $35,000 of her money into his bank account.

Per legal documents obtained by ET, the HGTV personality claimed, 'Josh was able to divert over $35,000 of my separate property rental income into his account.'

She went on to say in the court paperwork, 'I am asking for Josh to account for the funds taken and return them to me as those funds are specifically used to pay any loans, obligations, property taxes, insurance, and maintenance for these rental properties.'

Christina was previously married to Tarek El Moussa and they share daughter Taylor, 13, and son Brayden, eight.
